Sorry to see this was posted here first.  I think a similar post or /tell to a CE officer would have been replied to with the same sensitivity CE leadership has spoken with in this thread.<br>
Seeking IG resolution is preferable to airing dirty laundry.<br>
<br>
Be that as it may, the dirty laundry is out on the lawn now. All those peeking at it here (myself included) will talk about it regardless of if anyone was right or who was more wrong. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
There was obviously an aggro issue here, and a dispute over the mob that dropped the earring.  <br>
<br>
The KS issue itself should have been attempted to be resolved in game through diplomacy on the part of the alleged KS victim.  Speaking to the guild leadership of the alleged KS'er if face-face communications failed to give satisfaction.  THAT is the way to handle the situation.  A /petition and /report is another method, but one that usually leads to no clear resolution and leaves the victim even more unhappy.<br>
<br>
The alleged KS victim admits to ninja-looting here in this thread is a fact.  The KS itself will be shrouded in controversy, but in my opinion even if it did occur as the Ninja-looter states IT IS NOT justification for the ninja act.  There were many other ways to go about it.<br>
<br>
I empathize with the leadership of CE who now has a messy can of worms out in the public view &amp; an internal moral dilmena over the fate of one of their own. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
