It also seems to say that its ok to KS!<br>
<br>
I believe both of you .... to an extent. I believe that Alkan did KS, and Riaan has admited he looted it. but here is the Rub.<br>
<br>
KS (Kill Stealing) Is the act of attacking or Casting spells on a Mob that has allready Argoed or engaged another player, no matter what the reason. (This is from Verant)<br>
<br>
Ninja-Looting is when a player, loots an item that is thought of as valuable from the mob they did not kill.<br>
<br>
With KSing you Kill and Loot a mob that was not yours. (Reward: XP and Loot)<br>
With Ninja'ing you Loot a mob that was not yours. (Reward: Loot)<br>
<br>
Both of these practices is WRONG, and 2 wrongs do not make a right. but which one is more wrong? Which one is more right?<br>
<br>
1 person here had the mob argoed, (And the right to the loot) the second came in and KS'd (Stealing the XP) the first came back and looted the mob (Which he had argoed first)<br>
<br>
Its a bad situation, but I have no sympathie for a KSer<br>
